    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A single-page, vertical-scrolling "Event Hub" design. It starts with a hero section featuring a countdown to create urgency. This is followed by interactive cards for the three main activities (Live Stream, Pre-order, Warm-up Event) that scroll to detailed sections. It includes a visual timeline for the main event, clear calls-to-action for social media, and an interactive poll to boost user engagement. This structure was chosen to transform a static announcement into an exploratory and engaging experience, perfectly suited for a mobile-first social media audience. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: Event Start Date -> Goal: Create Urgency -> Viz/Presentation: Dynamic Countdown Timer (JS) -> Interaction: Real-time updates. Justification: Immediately grabs attention.
        - Report Info: Three Main Activities -> Goal: Organize/Inform -> Viz/Presentation: Interactive Cards (HTML/Tailwind) -> Interaction: Hover effects and smooth scroll to details. Justification: Cleanly structures information.
        - Report Info: Event Timeline (July 1-6) -> Goal: Inform -> Viz/Presentation: Visual Timeline (HTML/CSS) -> Interaction: None. Justification: More intuitive than a text list.
        - Report Info: User Poll -> Goal: Engage -> Viz/Presentation: Horizontal Bar Chart (Chart.js) -> Interaction: Buttons update chart data live. Justification: Creates a sense of community and participation.
        - CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
